# Epilogue profile: Complete set for dump/restore
#
# This profile defines which .env/local/ variables are transferred in the EPILOGUE
# section of a dump (after all protocol imports/adds/links complete).
#
# Purpose:
#   - Restores complete user environment configuration from OLD database
#   - Includes ALL variables (same as PROFILE_ALL)
#   - Applied AFTER restore completes, so function-specific interpreter overrides
#     don't interfere with the restore process itself
#
# Why separate from prologue?
#   - Prologue needs safe set (no function-specific interpreters) for restore to work
#   - Epilogue restores full customization after restore succeeds
#   - Example: If VPN_SWITCH_INTERPRETER_import=cat in prologue, restore would fail
#
# This is identical to PROFILE_ALL - includes every available variable.
#
# To regenerate this list after adding new variables:
#   cd template/environment
#   ls -1 | grep -v '^VPN_SWITCH_PROFILE_' | tr '\n' ' '
#
# Phase 3.1.4: Dump/restore prologue/epilogue separation
